##And I will sleep in peace #

567
00:41:51,709 --> 00:41:59,241
## Until you come #

568
00:41:59,316 --> 00:42:05,255
## To me ##

569
00:42:07,391 --> 00:42:10,189
- Who's winning?
- We are, for the nonce.

570
00:42:10,261 --> 00:42:14,425
- What's the "disposish"?
- Last night, four to one. Dana
Cudahy went up with the house.

571
00:42:14,498 --> 00:42:16,693
- And theirs?
- One burned.

572
00:42:16,767 --> 00:42:18,530
- The other three?
- Lead.

573
00:42:18,602 --> 00:42:20,627
- Whose?
- Leo's.

574
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:22,968
The old man's still
an artist with a Thompson.

575
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:25,031
[ Leo ]
Yeah, do that.

576
00:42:25,109 --> 00:42:29,045
Well, find him, goddamn it!
Go and see if he fell in the john.

577
00:42:30,514 --> 00:42:33,415
Son of a bitch. No chief.

578
00:42:33,484 --> 00:42:36,851
- Who's mindin' the goddamn store?
- Can't raise O'Doole?

579
00:42:36,921 --> 00:42:38,722
No, nor the mayor either.

580
00:42:38,722 --> 00:42:43,056
- That's not good.
They're running.
- They wouldn't dare!

581
00:42:43,127 --> 00:42:45,823
I don't know, Leo.
I warned you not to
hit Caspar's club.

582
00:42:45,930 --> 00:42:48,728
- I'm still here, ain't I?
- Caspar's play hurt you anyway.

583
00:42:48,799 --> 00:42:51,290
That sorry son of a bitch
just slit his own throat.

584
00:42:51,368 --> 00:42:54,496
Listen to me, Leo.
Last night made you
look vulnerable.

585
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:58,008
You don't hold elected office
in this town. You run it
because people think you run it.

586
00:42:58,075 --> 00:43:00,839
Once they stop thinking it,
you stop running it.

587
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:04,312
Jesus, Tom. It sounds like
a bad break for me
I wasn't killed!

588
00:43:04,381 --> 00:43:07,407
I mean it, Leo.
Start taking Caspar seriously.

589
00:43:07,518 --> 00:43:11,750
I know, I know.
Retreat to win, give up Bernie.
That'll solve all our problems.

590
00:43:11,822 --> 00:43:13,881
Won't anymore, I'll grant you that.

591
00:43:13,958 --> 00:43:16,426
But going toe-to-toe
with a psychopath
will get you nowhere.

592
00:43:16,493 --> 00:43:19,189
It'll force people
to choose sides just when
you're looking shaky.

593
00:43:19,263 --> 00:43:22,562
- The hell I do!
- Then where's the mayor?

594
00:43:22,666 --> 00:43:24,861
Why aren't there
any police here?

595
00:43:24,969 --> 00:43:26,960
Why weren't there any police
at your place last night?

596
00:43:27,071 --> 00:43:29,665
- I didn't ask for any.
- I did.

597
00:43:29,740 --> 00:43:32,732
[ Laughs ]

598
00:43:32,810 --> 00:43:35,608
Mother hen, huh?
What's the matter, Tommy?

599
00:43:35,679 --> 00:43:39,206
- Don't you think
I can take care of myself?
- I know you can't.

600
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:42,184
Here's the smart play, Leo.
You lay back, you give Bernie up,

601
00:43:42,252 --> 00:43:44,220
you let Caspar think
he's made his point.

602
00:43:44,321 --> 00:43:47,313
- Then you wait for him
to show a weakness.
- Please, Tom.

603
00:43:47,391 --> 00:43:49,621
You're sticking on Bernie.
You're sticking your neck out...

604
00:43:49,693 --> 00:43:52,628
for a guy who'd chop you off
at the heels if there
was two bits in it.

605
00:43:55,132 --> 00:43:57,828
[ Sighs ]
Tom,

606
00:43:57,901 --> 00:44:01,166
things aren't as, uh,
clear-cut as you make it.

607
00:44:02,806 --> 00:44:07,004
Bernie's- -
Well, hell, you know
about me and Verna.

608
00:44:07,077 --> 00:44:10,945
Things now are, uh--

609
00:44:11,015 --> 00:44:14,781
Not that I haven't
been a gentleman, but--

610
00:44:16,854 --> 00:44:20,312
I plan to ask her
to marry me, Tom.

611
00:44:25,062 --> 00:44:28,429
I guess you think
that's a bonehead play.

612
00:44:32,736 --> 00:44:36,536
- You think she wants you to?
- How the hell do I know?

613
00:44:36,607 --> 00:44:39,303
I think she does.
Yeah, of course she does.

614
00:44:39,410 --> 00:44:43,278
I know you think different,
but, well, we just, uh--

615
00:44:43,347 --> 00:44:45,713
We just differ on that.

616
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:51,682
Leo, Caspar didn't kill Rug.

617
00:44:51,755 --> 00:44:55,521
- Course he did.
- No. Think about it
just this one time.

618
00:44:55,592 --> 00:44:57,617
- Who was Rug following?
- Huh?

619
00:44:57,728 --> 00:45:01,186
It needn't have been that
sinister. Strange man follows
her down a dark alleyway.

620
00:45:01,298 --> 00:45:03,698
- I told you she can
look after herself.
- Verna wouldn't panic,

621
00:45:03,767 --> 00:45:06,964
shoot someone just because
he was following her.

622
00:45:07,037 --> 00:45:10,837
Nah, it wouldn't have happened
like that, and if it had
she would have told me.

623
00:45:10,908 --> 00:45:14,139
They pulled a .22 slug out of him.
A pop gun, Leo, a woman's gun.

624
00:45:14,211 --> 00:45:16,406
I know you don't
like her, Tom,

625
00:45:16,513 --> 00:45:19,482
but I trust Verna
as much as I trust you.

626
00:45:21,085 --> 00:45:23,019
Okay, Leo.

627
00:45:23,087 --> 00:45:25,385
Maybe it wasn't that innocent.

628
00:45:25,456 --> 00:45:29,119
Maybe Rug knew something
she didn't like him knowing
and wouldn't want you to know.

629
00:45:29,193 --> 00:45:32,856
Rug was following her.
Maybe he knew
where she was sleeping,

630
00:45:32,930 --> 00:45:34,864
and who with.

631
00:45:38,969 --> 00:45:41,460
Maybes don't make it so.

632
00:45:42,539 --> 00:45:44,530
There's more than maybes.

633
00:45:44,608 --> 00:45:48,169
You've trusted me before,
you've never lost anything
by it. Trust me on this.

634
00:45:50,981 --> 00:45:54,439
- This is too important.
- I don't ask much,
and I don't ask often.

635
00:45:54,551 --> 00:45:57,019
Trust me on this.

636
00:45:57,087 --> 00:46:00,352
- Tommy.
- Trust me on this,
or to hell with you.

637
00:46:02,926 --> 00:46:05,292
You don't mean that.

638
00:46:08,065 --> 00:46:09,999
She was with me...

639
00:46:10,067 --> 00:46:13,468
the night Rug
was following her,

640
00:46:13,570 --> 00:46:15,538
the night you dropped by.

641
00:46:17,107 --> 00:46:19,234
[ Scoffs ]

642
00:46:29,219 --> 00:46:31,551
Oh.

643
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:25,801
[ Grunts ]

644
00:47:38,255 --> 00:47:40,746
###[ Irish Tenor, Indistinct ]

645
00:47:50,067 --> 00:47:52,729
[ Woman Screams ]

646
00:48:17,461 --> 00:48:19,691
[ Screams ]

647
00:48:27,771 --> 00:48:30,535
Okay, Leo. Okay.
I'll throw him out.

648
00:48:32,676 --> 00:48:35,236
Yeah, do that.

649
00:48:36,313 --> 00:48:38,508
It's the kiss-off.

650
00:48:38,582 --> 00:48:41,915
If I never see him again,
it'll be soon enough.

651
00:48:45,222 --> 00:48:46,590
[ Dialing Phone ]

652
00:48:46,590 --> 00:48:47,852
[ Dialing Phone ]

653
00:48:52,296 --> 00:48:54,321
- Hello?
- Hello, Frankie.

654
00:48:54,398 --> 00:48:56,832
It's Tom.
How's the flunky business?

655
00:48:58,135 --> 00:49:00,399
I've had worse.
Your ventilator mending?

656
00:49:00,470 --> 00:49:03,564
- [ Knocking On Door ]
- Tell Caspar it's forgotten.

657
00:49:03,674 --> 00:49:06,108
- I'd like to see him.
- [ Knocking Continues ]

658
00:49:07,744 --> 00:49:09,974
Ah. All right, let me know.

659
00:49:54,791 --> 00:49:58,750
It worked, whatever you did.

660
00:49:58,829 --> 00:50:02,265
Leo says we're quits.

661
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:04,994
But you know I didn't have
anything to do with Rug.

662
00:50:05,102 --> 00:50:07,832
Maybe not.

663
00:50:07,904 --> 00:50:09,872
Anyway, that isn't
what soured him on you.

664
00:50:09,940 --> 00:50:12,272
Oh, you and me, huh?

665
00:50:14,044 --> 00:50:17,673
You always take
the long way around to get
what you want, don't you, Tom?

666
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:22,184
You could have just asked.

667
00:50:25,122 --> 00:50:28,023
What did I want?

668
00:50:28,091 --> 00:50:30,719
Me.

669
00:50:50,614 --> 00:50:53,139
[ Rings ]

670
00:50:56,787 --> 00:50:59,517
Yeah?

671
00:50:59,589 --> 00:51:01,489
Yeah, yeah.

672
00:51:01,558 --> 00:51:03,890
When?

673
00:51:03,960 --> 00:51:05,894
Okay.

674
00:51:10,734 --> 00:51:13,498
You still up?

675
00:51:13,570 --> 00:51:15,800
Yeah.

676
00:51:19,643 --> 00:51:22,703
What are you chewin' over?

677
00:51:22,813 --> 00:51:25,043
Dream I had once.

678
00:51:26,950 --> 00:51:29,919
I was walking in the woods.
I don't know why.

679
00:51:31,488 --> 00:51:34,616
Wind came whippin'.
Blew me hat off.

680
00:51:36,593 --> 00:51:39,562
And you chased it, right?

681
00:51:39,629 --> 00:51:42,029
You ran and ran.

682
00:51:42,099 --> 00:51:45,262
You finally caught up to it.

683
00:51:45,335 --> 00:51:49,431
And you picked it up,
but it wasn't a hat anymore.

684
00:51:49,506 --> 00:51:53,465
It had changed into something else,
something wonderful.

685
00:51:53,543 --> 00:51:56,376
No, it stayed a hat.

686
00:51:56,446 --> 00:51:58,937
And no, I didn't chase it.

687
00:52:00,317 --> 00:52:04,083
Nothing more foolish
than a man chasin' his hat.

688
00:52:04,154 --> 00:52:06,384
Where are you going?

689
00:52:06,456 --> 00:52:09,220
Just have to do a few things.

690
00:52:09,292 --> 00:52:12,750
- You and Leo might still
be able to patch things up.
- Me and Leo are finished.

691
00:52:12,829 --> 00:52:16,321
- Nothing's gonna change that.
- You never know.

692
00:52:16,433 --> 00:52:20,233
- He's got a big heart.
- We're quits as far as I'm
concerned, never mind him.

693
00:52:20,303 --> 00:52:24,569
And if Leo did want me back,
he's an even bigger sap
than I thought.

694
00:52:24,641 --> 00:52:27,132
Then why don't we just
pick up and leave town?

695
00:52:27,210 --> 00:52:30,077
There's nothing keeping you here.

696
00:52:30,147 --> 00:52:32,081
I know there's nothing keeping me.

697
00:52:32,149 --> 00:52:35,482
- What about Bernie?
- He could go with us.

698
00:52:36,753 --> 00:52:38,880
You, me and Bernie?
Where would we go, Verna?

699
00:52:38,989 --> 00:52:40,923
Niagara Falls?

700
00:52:40,991 --> 00:52:42,925
Why do you hate him?

701
00:52:42,993 --> 00:52:44,927
- I don't hate anyone.
- Or like anyone.

702
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:52,195
Where is Bernie?

703
00:52:52,269 --> 00:52:54,760
- Why?
- Leo can't protect him anymore.

704
00:52:54,871 --> 00:52:58,307
I oughta tell him to skip.

705
00:52:58,408 --> 00:53:00,342
The Royale, room 302.

706
00:53:05,549 --> 00:53:09,178
I guess we both
double-crossed Leo, huh?

707
00:53:09,252 --> 00:53:11,186
There's no gettin' around that.

708
00:53:12,322 --> 00:53:15,155
I guess he's well rid
of both of us.

709
00:53:15,225 --> 00:53:19,628
The two of us, we're about
bad enough to deserve each other.

710
00:53:23,099 --> 00:53:25,033
Are we?

711
00:53:27,137 --> 00:53:30,038
We're a couple of heels, Tom.

712
00:53:30,106 --> 00:53:32,802
Yes, we are.

713
00:53:33,009 --> 00:53:37,412
[ Caspar ] So he says,
"Screw him. Give him a dollar.
This was my idea. "

714
00:53:37,480 --> 00:53:41,211
[ Laughing ]
Hello, Tom.

715
00:53:41,284 --> 00:53:44,515
Uh, you know O'Doole
and the mayor.

716
00:53:44,588 --> 00:53:47,887
- Hello, boys.
- Tom's a big booster.
Always has been.

717
00:53:47,958 --> 00:53:52,054
That's fine, that's fine.
Well, Tom and I got
the proverbial fat to chew.

718
00:53:52,162 --> 00:53:54,960
- Just let us know
if you need anything.
- Yeah. Happy days.

719
00:53:55,031 --> 00:53:58,091
Have a seat, kid.
Yeah, that's it.

720
00:53:58,168 --> 00:54:01,433
So, you had enough time
to think about things?

721
00:54:01,504 --> 00:54:05,600
- Yeah, well, uh,
circumstances have changed.
- Don't I know it.

722
00:54:05,675 --> 00:54:08,769
Last night I know the Dane
was disappointed
the bulls showed up...

723
00:54:08,845 --> 00:54:11,507
before Frankie and Tic-Tac
really pinned your ears back,

724
00:54:11,615 --> 00:54:16,052
but I said, "Relax, Eddie.
I got a feeling about this kid.

725
00:54:16,152 --> 00:54:20,384
The kid and Leo
are gonna go bust-o.
Matter of time."

726
00:54:20,457 --> 00:54:23,153
I said, "The kid
is too smart for Leo."
That's what I said.

727
00:54:23,226 --> 00:54:26,286
Like a psychic.
Ask the Dane if I did.
Like a goddamn psychic.

728
00:54:26,363 --> 00:54:28,854
- Go ahead, ask him.
- You vouch for that
psychic business?

729
00:54:28,965 --> 00:54:31,490
- That's right, smart guy.
- I know you knew...

730
00:54:31,601 --> 00:54:34,627
protecting the shmatte
was a dumb idea.

731
00:54:34,704 --> 00:54:38,401
I know you've been wise
to all of Leo's dumb ideas lately.

732
00:54:38,475 --> 00:54:40,602
Only a matter of time-- bust-o.

733
00:54:40,677 --> 00:54:43,840
That's why last night
we didn't put the arm on you,
only Leo.

734
00:54:43,913 --> 00:54:47,440
Seeing how you squiffed
your play on Leo,
I can only be so grateful.

735
00:54:47,550 --> 00:54:51,816
- Oh, that's real brave coming
from Little Miss Punching Bag.
- Okay, Eddie.

736
00:54:51,888 --> 00:54:55,153
- Friends now, huh?
- Nuts.

737
00:54:56,826 --> 00:54:58,760
So, I guess you'll be
looking for a job, eh, kid?

738
00:54:58,828 --> 00:55:01,422
I might be.

739
00:55:01,498 --> 00:55:03,523
You got references?
You been to college?

740
00:55:03,600 --> 00:55:07,195
We only take yeggs
what's been to college.
Ain't that right, Dane?

741
00:55:07,304 --> 00:55:10,034
[ Laughs ]

742
00:55:10,106 --> 00:55:13,371
I'm joking, of course.
We all know you could be
useful to us,

743
00:55:13,443 --> 00:55:15,377
a smart kid such as yourself.

744
00:55:15,445 --> 00:55:19,245
The man who walks behind the man,
who whispers in his ear.

745
00:55:19,316 --> 00:55:22,979
- I guess you could be
useful in spades.
- Yeah, I can do plenty for you.

746
00:55:23,053 --> 00:55:27,513
- Can you get Leo off me?
- I'm tellin' you
not to worry about Leo.

747
00:55:27,590 --> 00:55:29,524
- We got plans for him.
- Oh, yeah?

748
00:55:29,592 --> 00:55:32,425
- Like what?
- Not so fast there, "kaputnik."

749
00:55:32,495 --> 00:55:35,020
I-I think what the Dane
is trying to say is,

750
00:55:35,098 --> 00:55:37,032
there'll be time
to talk about that.

751
00:55:37,100 --> 00:55:39,466
We can table that
for a later date.

752
00:55:40,937 --> 00:55:45,533
See, last time we jawed,
you gave me the high hat.

753
00:55:45,642 --> 00:55:48,133
I guess I'm sayin'...

754
00:55:48,244 --> 00:55:51,771
you gotta put something
on the table first.

755
00:55:51,848 --> 00:55:54,578
- Ante up.
- Fair enough. Where do we start?

756
00:55:54,651 --> 00:55:58,178
Hear that, Dane? All business.
I told you he was a good kid.

757
00:55:58,254 --> 00:56:00,449
"Where do we start?"
All business.

758
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:03,549
Well, we can start, for instance,
with the shmatte.

759
00:56:03,660 --> 00:56:05,628
Like, where's the shmatte?
You could maybe tell us that.

760
00:56:05,695 --> 00:56:10,019
The Royale, room 302.
And you might find Mink with him.

761
00:56:11,250 --> 00:56:13,217
[ Eddie ]
The hell you say.

762
00:56:13,284 --> 00:56:15,410
[ Tom ]
Sure. Bernie and Mink
are cozy as lice.

763
00:56:15,486 --> 00:56:18,784
- And it ain't just business.
- This guy is lying.

764
00:56:18,856 --> 00:56:20,789
- Why would I?
- This guy is wrong.

765
00:56:20,858 --> 00:56:27,363
This guy is all wrong.
Mink is clean and this clown
is a smart guy.

766
00:56:27,364 --> 00:56:29,388
It's easy enough to find out,
ain't it?

767
00:56:30,668 --> 00:56:35,104
You find Mink,
you bring him back here.

768
00:56:36,807 --> 00:56:40,765
Go to the car.
I'm gonna send Frankie and
Tic-Tac with you to the Royale.

769
00:56:40,846 --> 00:56:43,109
If Bernie's there,

770
00:56:43,181 --> 00:56:45,546
Frankie and Tic-Tac'll
take care of him.

771
00:56:45,617 --> 00:56:48,016
And if he's not there?

772
00:56:48,120 --> 00:56:51,555
I'll sit facing the corner
in a funny hat.

773
00:56:53,191 --> 00:56:55,886
- [ Screams ]
- Get your little hebe ass
in the car.

774
00:56:55,961 --> 00:56:58,053
- [ Tic-Tac] Let's go.
- [ Frankie ]
Come on, you skel.

775
00:56:58,130 --> 00:57:00,222
[ Bernie ]
What are you doing to me?

776
00:57:00,299 --> 00:57:02,357
- We're going to
Miller's Crossing.
- I didn't do- - Tom! Tom!

777
00:57:02,434 --> 00:57:04,867
- Lock him up.
Jesus! Are you part of this?

778
00:57:04,936 --> 00:57:07,130
- Sit still, hymie.
- You can't be part of this.

779
00:57:07,240 --> 00:57:09,867
I think these guys
are gonna whack me!
Tom, you gotta talk to 'em!

780
00:57:09,976 --> 00:57:12,910
- You're giving me a headache,
you little sheeny. Let's go!
- Talk to 'em!

781
00:57:15,880 --> 00:57:18,245
[ Bernie ]
Get me outta here!

782
00:57:18,316 --> 00:57:20,783
Oh, Tommy.!

783
00:57:20,852 --> 00:57:22,876
- [ Frankie ]
Get him outta here!
- [ Bernie ] Frankie!

784
00:57:22,954 --> 00:57:25,854
- Come on! Come on!
- [ Blubbering ]

785
00:57:28,260 --> 00:57:30,318
- Tic-Tac!
- Quiet him down!

786
00:57:30,428 --> 00:57:32,361
Uuh!

787
00:57:32,431 --> 00:57:34,557
- Get up, you skel!
- [ Groans ]

788
00:57:34,633 --> 00:57:36,725
- Come on.
- Frankie, no!

789
00:57:36,803 --> 00:57:40,260
- Get up, you son of a bitch.
- Frank-- Aah!

790
00:57:40,339 --> 00:57:42,932
- Oh, Frankie!
- Get up, you kike!

791
00:57:43,009 --> 00:57:46,944
[ Tic-Tac ]
Okay, take him in the woods
and whack him.

792
00:57:47,013 --> 00:57:49,242
- What?
- That's right.

793
00:57:49,315 --> 00:57:52,283
The boss wants you to do it.
Make sure you're with the good guys.

794
00:57:52,351 --> 00:57:55,183
- You know how to do this, right?
- You little yid! Get up!

795
00:57:55,254 --> 00:57:57,346
Ya gotta remember
to put one in his brain.

796
00:57:57,423 --> 00:58:00,448
Your first shot puts him down.
Then you put one in his brain.

797
00:58:00,526 --> 00:58:02,550
Then he's dead.
Then we go home.

798
00:58:02,628 --> 00:58:06,188
[ Struggling,
Blubbering Continues ]

799
00:58:06,299 --> 00:58:08,528
Get up and walk.

800
00:58:08,602 --> 00:58:10,865
I can't get up. I can't get up.

801
00:58:10,937 --> 00:58:16,135
- Get up and walk,
you pissing little yid!
- [ Tic-Tac ] Let's go!

802
00:58:36,062 --> 00:58:39,121
Tommy, you can't do this.
You don't bump guys.

803
00:58:39,198 --> 00:58:41,529
You're not like
those animals back there.

804
00:58:43,971 --> 00:58:46,200
It's not right, Tom.

805
00:58:46,272 --> 00:58:48,705
They can't make us do this.

806
00:58:48,774 --> 00:58:53,005
It's a wrong situation.
They can't make us
different people than we are.

807
00:58:53,079 --> 00:58:55,012
We're not muscle.
I never killed anybody.

808
00:58:55,082 --> 00:58:57,675
I used a little information
for a chisel, that's all.

809
00:58:57,751 --> 00:59:00,412
It's my nature, Tom.
I can't help it.

810
00:59:00,520 --> 00:59:04,285
Somebody hands me an angle,
I play it. I don't deserve
to die for that.

811
00:59:04,358 --> 00:59:06,291
Do you think I do?

812
00:59:08,028 --> 00:59:11,724
I'm just a grifter.
Huh, Tom? I'm a nobody!

813
00:59:11,798 --> 00:59:15,289
But I tell you what- -
I never crossed a friend.

814
00:59:15,369 --> 00:59:17,734
I never killed anybody,
I never crossed a friend.

815
00:59:17,804 --> 00:59:19,771
We're not like those animals.

816
00:59:19,841 --> 00:59:21,774
This is not us.

817
00:59:21,842 --> 00:59:24,503
[ Stammering ]
This is a dream!

818
00:59:24,577 --> 00:59:27,739
It's a dream, Tommy!
I'm praying to you!

819
00:59:27,813 --> 00:59:29,780
I can't die.

820
00:59:29,850 --> 00:59:31,783
I can't die...

821
00:59:31,851 --> 00:59:35,581
out here in the woods
like a dumb animal.

822
00:59:35,656 --> 00:59:38,089
In the woods like a dumb animal!

823
00:59:38,190 --> 00:59:41,158
Like a--
Like a dumb animal!

824
00:59:41,228 --> 00:59:44,958
I can't- -
I can't- - I can't die
out here in the woods...

825
00:59:45,033 --> 00:59:47,626
like a dumb animal.
[ Sobbing ]

826
00:59:47,701 --> 00:59:51,101
I can't... die!

827
00:59:54,909 --> 00:59:56,842
I'm praying to you.

828
00:59:58,813 --> 01:00:01,337
Look in your heart.

829
01:00:01,449 --> 01:00:03,541
I'm praying to you.

830
01:00:04,786 --> 01:00:09,051
Look in your heart.
I'm praying to you.

831
01:00:09,123 --> 01:00:11,818
Look in your heart.

832
01:00:11,893 --> 01:00:15,259
I'm praying to you!

833
01:00:15,330 --> 01:00:17,422
Look in your heart!

834
01:00:18,933 --> 01:00:22,129
I'm praying to you!
Look in your heart.

835
01:00:22,203 --> 01:00:25,330
I'm praying to you!

836
01:00:25,406 --> 01:00:29,705
Look in your heart!
Look in your heart!

837
01:00:29,776 --> 01:00:32,039
You can't kill me.

838
01:00:32,112 --> 01:00:35,012
- Look in your heart.
- [ Gun Fires ]

839
01:00:50,298 --> 01:00:53,289
- Tommy--
- Shut up. You're dead. Get me?

840
01:00:55,937 --> 01:00:58,496
I understand. I'm dead.

841
01:00:58,606 --> 01:01:01,039
- God bless you.
- Shut up.

842
01:01:01,109 --> 01:01:04,441
You have to disappear for good.
No one can see you.
No one can know.

843
01:01:04,512 --> 01:01:07,776
- God bless you.
- Go somewhere no one knows you.

844
01:01:07,849 --> 01:01:11,306
Anyone sees you,
you really are dead.
You're not my problem anymore.

845
01:01:11,386 --> 01:01:13,819
Of course not.
You've done your share. Thank you.

846
01:01:13,922 --> 01:01:16,890
- Don't worry. I understand.
- Shut up. Shut up.

847
01:01:16,959 --> 01:01:20,587
- Thank you.
- Shut up. Get out of here
before I change my mind.

848
01:01:20,662 --> 01:01:23,129
[ Whispers ]
God bless you.

849
01:01:40,782 --> 01:01:42,715
[ Frankie Coughs ]

850
01:01:45,687 --> 01:01:48,416
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

851
01:01:54,295 --> 01:01:56,228
[ Frankie ]
Put one in his brain?

852
01:01:57,398 --> 01:01:59,490
- Yeah.
- [ Tic-Tac ]
Atta boy.

853
01:02:05,207 --> 01:02:07,436
[ Laughing ]

854
01:02:14,284 --> 01:02:16,217
[ Streetcar Rumbling ]

855
01:02:16,285 --> 01:02:18,582
Mink? Tom Reagan.
Where you been?

856
01:02:18,655 --> 01:02:20,747
[ Mink On Phone, Indistinct ]

857
01:02:25,028 --> 01:02:27,894
Will you look?
Eddie Dane's been looking for you.

858
01:02:27,964 --> 01:02:29,931
- Bernie's dead.
- Jesus Christ!

859
01:02:29,999 --> 01:02:34,264
Stop wailing and listen to me.
Caspar knows you were
in on selling out his fix.

860
01:02:34,337 --> 01:02:36,600
- Who the hell
gave him that idea?
- Heh!

861
01:02:36,672 --> 01:02:40,266
- I guess I gave him that idea.
Sorry. It just slipped out.
- What are you trying to do?

862
01:02:40,342 --> 01:02:43,276
Shut up and let me talk.
You lay low till Caspar
cools off.

863
01:02:43,346 --> 01:02:48,112
Then tell him the Dane was in
on the sellout, and I'll
make Caspar go easy on you.

864
01:02:48,217 --> 01:02:51,151
- You got me into this mess.
- That's right, I got you into this.

865
01:02:51,220 --> 01:02:54,780
- Just remember, Mink, I'm the
only one who can get you out.
- Wait a minute, Tom.

866
01:02:54,857 --> 01:02:57,723
Waah! Uuh!

867
01:03:04,567 --> 01:03:08,559
Hello, Terry.
Getting out the vote?

868
01:03:08,671 --> 01:03:14,302
A message from Leo.
Leo says if you're smart
you'll sit this one out,

869
01:03:14,377 --> 01:03:16,867
not that he cares one way
or the other.

870
01:03:16,946 --> 01:03:21,473
Leo says if you're on
the wrong side you take
your chances like anybody else.

871
01:03:21,551 --> 01:03:23,986
Leo says he gives
no special favors, that's all.

872
01:03:23,987 --> 01:03:26,887
Tell Leo he's not God
on the throne.

873
01:03:26,956 --> 01:03:30,584
He's just a cheap political boss
with more hair tonic than brains.

874
01:03:30,693 --> 01:03:34,287
[ Groans ]
Uhh!

875
01:03:36,934 --> 01:03:39,026
Did Leo say that as well?

876
01:03:39,103 --> 01:03:41,036
No, I said that.

877
01:03:42,205 --> 01:03:44,638
Cross Leo,
next time I'll say plenty.

878
01:03:46,576 --> 01:03:50,671
[ Car's Doors Shut,
Departs ]

879
01:03:51,915 --> 01:03:54,849
When you're right, you're right.

880
01:03:54,919 --> 01:03:58,217
But you never say,
"I told you so."

881
01:03:58,289 --> 01:04:00,381
[ Tom ]
So what am I right about?

882
01:04:01,792 --> 01:04:04,385
Well, I'll tell you.

883
01:04:04,461 --> 01:04:08,294
But first you gotta promise
not to say I told you so.

884
01:04:08,399 --> 01:04:12,528
I never say that,
and I don't like people who do.

885
01:04:15,172 --> 01:04:17,503
Mink was robbing me
right along with the shmatte.

886
01:04:17,575 --> 01:04:19,508
What convinced you of that?

887
01:04:19,577 --> 01:04:21,874
Mink took a powder.
We can't find him.

888
01:04:21,946 --> 01:04:24,379
The Dane, he's making
excuses for him.

889
01:04:24,448 --> 01:04:26,915
But personally,
I think you was right.

890
01:04:26,985 --> 01:04:29,578
I think that Mink and Bernie
was in it together.

891
01:04:29,687 --> 01:04:33,122
I think Mink heard
that you bumped
the shmatte and lit out.

892
01:04:33,191 --> 01:04:35,488
Lousy son of a bitch.

893
01:04:37,195 --> 01:04:40,721
- I told you so.
- What?

894
01:04:40,799 --> 01:04:42,732
[ Laughs ]

895
01:04:42,801 --> 01:04:46,702
You got a lip on you.
That's all right.

896
01:04:46,770 --> 01:04:49,829
I don't generally care for it,
but that's all right.

897
01:04:51,208 --> 01:04:54,142
You was a good sport
to bump the shmatte.

898
01:04:55,212 --> 01:04:57,304
How do you know
Mink skipped?

899
01:04:57,381 --> 01:05:00,213
- Because the Dane can't find him.
- So he says.

900
01:05:00,284 --> 01:05:04,310
- Meaning what exactly?
- Maybe nothing.

901
01:05:04,421 --> 01:05:08,447
I didn't give it much thought,
'cause a guy'll say anything
when his number is up.

902
01:05:08,559 --> 01:05:11,288
But, uh, just before
I bumped Bernie,

903
01:05:11,362 --> 01:05:14,455
he swore to me
that Eddie Dane and Mink
were setting him up- -

904
01:05:14,531 --> 01:05:17,465
that they were the ones
who sold out your fix.

905
01:05:26,077 --> 01:05:28,010
Well, uh--

906
01:05:28,079 --> 01:05:30,410
Well, like you say, uh,
a guy'll say anything.

907
01:05:30,482 --> 01:05:32,915
So why isn't
Eddie Dane here?

908
01:05:34,687 --> 01:05:37,314
Well, he don't
care for you, kid.

909
01:05:38,391 --> 01:05:41,325
Maybe it's only fair to tell you.

910
01:05:41,427 --> 01:05:44,884
After you left us,
he tried to sell me
on a double-cross.

911
01:05:44,997 --> 01:05:47,897
He says to me,
why don't we double-cross you
and give you the bump...

912
01:05:47,967 --> 01:05:49,900
after we get the shmatte.

913
01:05:49,967 --> 01:05:53,959
Well, I figure a deal's a deal.
You're square with me.

914
01:05:54,039 --> 01:05:58,771
You bump the shmatte,
I hold up my end.
It's a question of ethics.

915
01:05:58,843 --> 01:06:03,074
Everything above board so
everybody knows who's a friend,
who's an enemy.

916
01:06:04,482 --> 01:06:07,678
So the Dane doesn't like you,
but he wouldn't cross me.

917
01:06:07,752 --> 01:06:09,685
We go back.

918
01:06:11,589 --> 01:06:16,685
Of course there's always
that wild card when,
uh, love is involved.

919
01:06:19,431 --> 01:06:21,898
I know Mink
is Eddie Dane's boy.

920
01:06:23,903 --> 01:06:26,462
Still, l--
I don't make it that way.

921
01:06:28,307 --> 01:06:31,673
- Then there's nothing
to worry about.
- Yeah.

922
01:06:31,744 --> 01:06:36,077
Papa, Papa, I got a prize
from the sister! Papa, Papa,
I got a prize from the sister!

923
01:06:36,148 --> 01:06:39,548
- Papa, Papa, I got a prize
from the sister!
- Yeah. Just a minute.

924
01:06:39,652 --> 01:06:41,812
- Of course, then, there's
no reason-- Shut up!
- Papa, Papa, I got--

925
01:06:41,921 --> 01:06:45,321
You take a page
out of this guy's book.

926
01:06:45,391 --> 01:06:49,417
- A little less you talk,
a little more you think!
- [ Bawling ]

927
01:06:51,697 --> 01:06:54,062
Kids. You gotta be firm.

928
01:06:54,132 --> 01:06:58,864
Anyways, there's no reason
not to check things out.

929
01:06:58,971 --> 01:07:02,374
If Mink is around,
I want you to find him.
He can tell us what's what.

930
01:07:02,375 --> 01:07:05,434
What's the matter?
Somebody hit you?

931
01:07:05,511 --> 01:07:08,343
What's the matter?
Aren't we friends anymore?

932
01:07:08,414 --> 01:07:11,348
If you find him,
I wanna talk to him alone.

933
01:07:11,416 --> 01:07:14,043
That's the way you get
the straight dope- -man to man.

934
01:07:14,120 --> 01:07:17,816
Just me, Mink...
and my friend Roscoe.

935
01:07:17,923 --> 01:07:20,584
You understand
what I'm saying?

936
01:07:20,659 --> 01:07:23,092
- It ain't complicated.
- [ Boy Howling ]

937
01:07:33,806 --> 01:07:38,265
You should leave town
for a few days. Things are
gonna heat up around here.

938
01:07:38,378 --> 01:07:40,811
Go to the Palisades.
I'll join you soon as I'm done.

939
01:07:40,881 --> 01:07:43,815
I can't find Bernie.
Did you find him?

940
01:07:45,118 --> 01:07:47,051
Yeah.

941
01:07:47,119 --> 01:07:49,313
Is he leaving?

942
01:07:49,389 --> 01:07:53,757
He, uh-- He left.

943
01:07:53,828 --> 01:07:56,421
- He say where to?
- He didn't say.

944
01:07:56,530 --> 01:07:58,724
- You--
- Thanks.

945
01:08:12,311 --> 01:08:15,677
- [ Dane ] What's that
potato-eater up to?
- [ Thug ] Beats me.

946
01:08:15,748 --> 01:08:18,215
- That's Bernie's sister, ain't it?
- Beats me.

947
01:08:18,285 --> 01:08:20,684
- What's he seeing her for?
- Beats me. Maybe--

948
01:08:20,754 --> 01:08:24,519
Shut up. Get lost.

949
01:08:24,591 --> 01:08:27,150
I'll see where
the twist flops.

950
01:08:28,361 --> 01:08:31,852
You know who I am?

951
01:08:31,932 --> 01:08:34,593
Yeah, Johnny Caspar's shadow.
What, did he stay in bed today?

952
01:08:34,701 --> 01:08:38,693
Jesus. I open my mouth,
the whole world turns smart.

953
01:08:38,772 --> 01:08:42,298
- You're Leo's twist, right?
- Me and Leo are through.

954
01:08:42,376 --> 01:08:45,139
Yeah?
So you're sluttin' around
with Tom now, huh?

955
01:08:45,212 --> 01:08:47,975
You get outta here.

956
01:08:48,048 --> 01:08:50,345
Okay. See you later.

957
01:08:52,453 --> 01:08:54,886
Before I go,
what's your boyfriend up to?

958
01:08:54,955 --> 01:08:57,081
- Nothing I know about.
- Yeah?

959
01:08:57,158 --> 01:08:59,250
That doesn't
figure for me--

960
01:08:59,327 --> 01:09:02,386
you dumpin' Leo for the guy
who put a bullet in your brother.

961
01:09:06,366 --> 01:09:10,961
He didn't tell you. Aww.

962
01:09:11,071 --> 01:09:13,004
Spin her, Eddie.

963
01:09:14,107 --> 01:09:16,574
Ooh!

964
01:09:25,319 --> 01:09:27,684
[ Straining ]

965
01:09:32,693 --> 01:09:36,856
- You Leo's?
- Yeah. He wanted her
looked-out for.

966
01:09:36,931 --> 01:09:41,128
Well, you did a bang-upjob.
I'll be sure to tell him.

967
01:09:41,202 --> 01:09:45,262
- Where's Leo?
- If I tell you, how do I know
you won't kill me?

968
01:09:45,339 --> 01:09:50,503
Because if you told me and I
killed you and you were lying,
I wouldn't get to kill you then.

969
01:09:50,612 --> 01:09:53,307
- Where's Leo?
- He's moving around.

970
01:09:53,381 --> 01:09:57,476
- He's getting his mob together
tomorrow at Whiskey Nick's.
- You sure?

971
01:09:57,553 --> 01:09:59,486
Check it. It's gold.

972
01:09:59,554 --> 01:10:03,148
You know what, yegg?
I believe you.

973
01:10:25,079 --> 01:10:27,103
Go ahead and run, sweetie.

974
01:10:27,182 --> 01:10:30,673
I'll track down
all of you whores.

975
01:10:35,657 --> 01:10:37,590
[ Knocking ]

976
01:10:43,599 --> 01:10:45,532
[ Doorknob Rattling ]

977
01:10:56,178 --> 01:10:58,111
[ Door Opens ]

978
01:11:01,083 --> 01:11:02,947
[ Door Closes ]

979
01:11:30,713 --> 01:11:34,478
Hello, Bernie. Come on in.
Make yourself at home.

980
01:11:34,550 --> 01:11:37,541
Hello, Tom.

981
01:11:37,654 --> 01:11:41,419
I thought I'd do that,
since you didn't seem to be in.

982
01:11:41,491 --> 01:11:45,654
Figured it was a bad idea
to wait in the hall, seeing
as I'm supposed to be dead.

983
01:11:48,765 --> 01:11:51,198
How'd you know it was me?

984
01:11:51,267 --> 01:11:53,757
You're the only one I know
who'd knock and then break in.

985
01:11:53,870 --> 01:11:55,837
Your other friends
wouldn't break in?

986
01:11:55,938 --> 01:11:59,134
My other friends
want to kill me,
so they wouldn't knock.

987
01:11:59,208 --> 01:12:01,641
What's on your mind. Bernie?

988
01:12:03,980 --> 01:12:06,379
Things.

989
01:12:06,450 --> 01:12:11,910
I guess you must be angry.
I'm supposed to be
gone far away.

990
01:12:11,988 --> 01:12:15,081
I guess it seems sort of
irresponsible, my being here.

991
01:12:17,627 --> 01:12:21,118
And I was gonna leave.
Honest, I was.

992
01:12:21,197 --> 01:12:23,130
But then I started thinking...

993
01:12:23,199 --> 01:12:26,065
if I stuck around,
that would not be good for you.

994
01:12:26,135 --> 01:12:28,864
Then I started
thinking that--

995
01:12:28,938 --> 01:12:31,371
that might not
be bad for me.

996
01:12:32,642 --> 01:12:34,575
[ Chuckles ]

997
01:12:34,644 --> 01:12:37,373
You didn't see
the play you gave me.

998
01:12:37,447 --> 01:12:39,710
I mean, what am I gonna do?

999
01:12:39,782 --> 01:12:42,716
If I leave, I got nothing.

1000
01:12:42,786 --> 01:12:45,515
No money, no friends, nothing.

1001
01:12:45,589 --> 01:12:47,749
If I stay, I got you.

1002
01:12:47,824 --> 01:12:52,351
Anyone finds out I'm alive,
you're dead, so...

1003
01:12:54,530 --> 01:12:56,520
I got-- I got you, Tommy.

1004
01:12:59,069 --> 01:13:02,401
What's the matter?
You got nothing
to crack wise about?

1005
01:13:02,473 --> 01:13:04,906
Bernie ain't
so funny anymore?

1006
01:13:08,178 --> 01:13:11,146
I guess I made kind of
a fool of myself out there...

1007
01:13:13,350 --> 01:13:15,817
bawling away like a twist.

1008
01:13:15,919 --> 01:13:18,352
I guess--

1009
01:13:18,423 --> 01:13:20,356
I guess I turned yellow.

1010
01:13:20,423 --> 01:13:24,119
- You didn't tell anyone
about that?
- No.

1011
01:13:24,194 --> 01:13:26,388
Of course,
you know about it.

1012
01:13:30,367 --> 01:13:32,493
It's a painful memory...

1013
01:13:34,438 --> 01:13:39,272
and I can't help remembering
that you put the finger on me,

1014
01:13:39,343 --> 01:13:42,436
and you took me out there
to whack me.

1015
01:13:42,513 --> 01:13:46,141
I know... you didn't.
I know.

1016
01:13:46,216 --> 01:13:50,049
- You didn't shoot me, but--
- But what have I done
for you lately?

1017
01:13:50,121 --> 01:13:52,145
Don't smart me.

1018
01:13:53,725 --> 01:13:56,158
See, I want
to watch you squirm.

1019
01:13:57,729 --> 01:14:00,162
I want to see you
sweat a little.

1020
01:14:02,065 --> 01:14:04,089
And when you smart me...

1021
01:14:05,636 --> 01:14:08,103
it ruins it.

1022
01:14:17,949 --> 01:14:20,382
There's one other thing I want.

1023
01:14:22,288 --> 01:14:25,051
I want to seeJohnny Caspar
cold and stiff.

1024
01:14:25,122 --> 01:14:28,557
That's what you'll do
for your friend Bernie.

1025
01:14:31,662 --> 01:14:34,926
In the meantime,
I'll stay out of sight.

1026
01:14:34,998 --> 01:14:38,433
But if Caspar ain't stiff
in a couple of days...

1027
01:14:38,503 --> 01:14:40,595
I start eating
in restaurants.

1028
01:14:54,520 --> 01:14:56,749
Oof! .

1029
01:15:00,592 --> 01:15:03,355
Uuh!

1030
01:15:03,461 --> 01:15:05,519
You make me laugh, Tommy.

1031
01:15:05,631 --> 01:15:09,191
You're gonna catch cold.
Then you're no good to me.

1032
01:15:09,268 --> 01:15:12,202
What were you gonna do
if you caught me?

1033
01:15:12,271 --> 01:15:15,706
I'd just squirt a few,
and then you'd let me go again.

1034
01:15:22,715 --> 01:15:26,081
Hello, Tad.
How's the club holding up?

1035
01:15:26,151 --> 01:15:29,847
We're managing to squeak by
without you.
Got Lazarre's money?

1036
01:15:29,921 --> 01:15:33,014
- No.
- You're not supposed to be here
since you turned rat.

1037
01:15:33,091 --> 01:15:35,650
Relax, Tad.
Leo isn't around, is he?

1038
01:15:35,727 --> 01:15:39,822
Last couple of days you booked
any heavy bets on a long shot
at Saturday's fights?

1039
01:15:39,899 --> 01:15:41,957
Why the hell
should I tell you?

1040
01:15:42,066 --> 01:15:45,933
The truth is, Tad,
no reason on Earth.

1041
01:15:48,507 --> 01:15:50,497
Saturday's fights?

1042
01:15:50,576 --> 01:15:54,534
DropJohnson put two grand
on one yesterday- -

1043
01:15:54,613 --> 01:15:58,048
on Sailor Reese,
an undercard bum.

1044
01:15:58,117 --> 01:16:01,176
DropJohnson.
He play your book much?

1045
01:16:01,287 --> 01:16:04,517
- Are you kidding? I didn't
even know he could count.
- [ Woman Screams ]

1046
01:16:04,590 --> 01:16:06,853
Jesus. You bring them with you?

1047
01:16:06,926 --> 01:16:10,326
Hello, Brian.
Still fighting the good fight?

1048
01:16:10,396 --> 01:16:12,693
Hello, Tom.
Neither rain nor wind nor snow.

1049
01:16:12,766 --> 01:16:14,858
That's the mailman. O'Doole here?

1050
01:16:21,373 --> 01:16:24,307
Hello, O'Doole.
You don't look happy.

1051
01:16:24,376 --> 01:16:26,502
Look at this mess.

1052
01:16:26,579 --> 01:16:29,877
Guttin' the golden calf again.
I don't know whether to laugh or cry.

1053
01:16:29,950 --> 01:16:33,646
Yeah, it's awful confusing.
You know a yegg
named DropJohnson?

1054
01:16:33,719 --> 01:16:36,516
- We spanked him
a couple of times.
- Where does he flop?

1055
01:16:36,588 --> 01:16:38,782
- Terminal Hotel, Bay Street.
- [ Gunshot ]

1056
01:16:38,891 --> 01:16:43,293
Jesus!
Look, don't nobody ask me since
I'm just the chief around here,

1057
01:16:43,362 --> 01:16:45,454
but I'll tell you my opinion.

1058
01:16:45,532 --> 01:16:49,900
Caspar is just as crazy as Leo,
and an "eye-tie"
into the bargain.

1059
01:16:49,969 --> 01:16:53,131
What's the matter, O'Doole?
Doesn't anything ever suit you?

1060
01:17:03,316 --> 01:17:06,113
Hop in, Tom.
We been lookin'for you.

1061
01:17:06,186 --> 01:17:08,585
- I'm busy.
- Hop in anyway.

1062
01:17:08,655 --> 01:17:11,919
You can't hijack me, Tic-Tac.
We're on the same side now.

1063
01:17:11,992 --> 01:17:14,789
Or didn't you get
that far in school?

1064
01:17:24,171 --> 01:17:26,035
How'd you get the fat lip?

1065
01:17:26,106 --> 01:17:30,474
- Old war wound.
Acts up around morons.
- Very smart.

1066
01:17:30,544 --> 01:17:33,671
What were you doing
at the club, talking
things over with Leo?

1067
01:17:33,748 --> 01:17:36,716
Don't think so hard, Eddie.
You might sprain something.

1068
01:17:36,783 --> 01:17:39,512
You are so goddamn smart.

1069
01:17:39,586 --> 01:17:41,519
Except you ain't.

1070
01:17:41,588 --> 01:17:44,556
I get you, smart guy.
I know what you are.

1071
01:17:44,624 --> 01:17:46,557
Straight as a corkscrew.

1072
01:17:46,626 --> 01:17:48,559
Mr. Inside Out-ski,

1073
01:17:48,628 --> 01:17:52,757
like some goddamn Bolshevik
picking up his orders
from Yegg Central.

1074
01:17:52,833 --> 01:17:54,925
You think you're
so goddamn smart.

1075
01:17:55,035 --> 01:17:57,195
You join upJohnny Caspar,

1076
01:17:57,303 --> 01:17:59,361
you bump Bernie Bernbaum.

1077
01:18:00,607 --> 01:18:03,939
Up is down. Black is white.

1078
01:18:05,278 --> 01:18:08,337
Well, I think you're half smart.

1079
01:18:08,415 --> 01:18:11,008
I think you were straight
with your frail,

1080
01:18:11,085 --> 01:18:13,678
I think you were queer
with Johnny Caspar...

1081
01:18:13,788 --> 01:18:17,985
and I think you'd sooner
join a ladies' league
than gun a guy down.

1082
01:18:18,059 --> 01:18:22,461
Then I hear from these
two geniuses they never even
saw this rub-out take place.

1083
01:18:22,530 --> 01:18:26,032
- Boss said to have him do it.
He didn't say nothing about--
- Shut up!

1084
01:18:26,033 --> 01:18:29,195
Or maybe you still got
too many teeth.

1085
01:18:31,807 --> 01:18:36,004
Everyone is so goddamn smart.

1086
01:18:36,111 --> 01:18:39,876
Well, we'll go out
to Miller's Crossing...

1087
01:18:39,946 --> 01:18:42,880
and we'll see who's smart.

1088
01:18:47,253 --> 01:18:49,777
###[ Frankie Singing
In Italian ]

1089
01:19:07,008 --> 01:19:11,205
You understand if we don't
find a stiff out here,
we leave a fresh one.

1090
01:19:28,263 --> 01:19:31,197
Where are your friends
when you need 'em, huh?

1091
01:19:32,467 --> 01:19:34,900
Where's Leo now?

1092
01:19:36,873 --> 01:19:39,306
Hey, Tic-Tac!

1093
01:19:39,375 --> 01:19:43,208
You ever notice how
the snappy dialogue dries up...

1094
01:19:43,279 --> 01:19:45,838
once a guy starts
soiling his union suit?

1095
01:19:45,914 --> 01:19:48,347
[ Chuckling ]

1096
01:19:53,288 --> 01:19:55,380
###[ Continues ]

1097
01:20:02,130 --> 01:20:04,097
## [ Stops ]

1098
01:20:06,835 --> 01:20:08,995
## [ Resumes ]

1099
01:20:21,517 --> 01:20:24,212
[ Retching ]

1100
01:20:29,692 --> 01:20:33,957
Okay. There's nothing out here.

1101
01:20:34,029 --> 01:20:38,829
###[ Stops ]

1102
01:20:38,901 --> 01:20:42,597
###[ Resumes ]

1103
01:20:47,043 --> 01:20:51,843
- [ Groans ]
- Think about this... smart guy.

1104
01:20:51,913 --> 01:20:54,813
[ Tic-Tac ]
It's hanky time.

1105
01:20:56,785 --> 01:20:59,514
[ Coughing ]

1106
01:20:59,588 --> 01:21:02,852
- ## [ Stops ]
- Birds have been at him.

1107
01:21:02,924 --> 01:21:05,414
Jesus Christ.

1108
01:21:05,528 --> 01:21:07,995
[ Grunts ]

1109
01:21:17,306 --> 01:21:19,637
[ Coughing Continues ]

1110
01:21:30,120 --> 01:21:34,055
Told you
to put one in his brain,
not in his stinkin' face!

1111
01:21:34,124 --> 01:21:36,216
[ Wheezing Laughter ]

1112
01:21:38,061 --> 01:21:41,791
[ Frankie ]
I told you, Dane.
We heard two shots.

1113
01:21:48,972 --> 01:21:51,303
[ Man, Woman Arguing,
Indistinct ]

1114
01:22:09,359 --> 01:22:11,451
Hello, Drop.

1115
01:22:15,165 --> 01:22:17,598
How are the Katzenjammers?

1116
01:22:17,667 --> 01:22:20,396
Hello, Tom. What's the rumpus?

1117
01:22:21,805 --> 01:22:23,965
Had any visitors?

1118
01:22:24,074 --> 01:22:26,132
Uhh, no.

1119
01:22:26,243 --> 01:22:28,176
Not ever, Drop?

1120
01:22:28,245 --> 01:22:30,235
Not lately.

1121
01:22:30,314 --> 01:22:32,873
Then you must be happy to see me.

1122
01:22:36,019 --> 01:22:37,952
So, uh...

1123
01:22:38,022 --> 01:22:41,923
you didn't see Bernie Bernbaum
before he was shown across.

1124
01:22:41,993 --> 01:22:43,983
Uh, no.

1125
01:22:44,095 --> 01:22:46,153
Seen him since?

1126
01:22:48,266 --> 01:22:50,597
One last question, Drop.

1127
01:22:50,668 --> 01:22:55,263
You got a lot of money
on tomorrow's fight.

1128
01:22:55,340 --> 01:22:59,503
That your bet, or, uh...
you placing it for a friend?

1129
01:22:59,609 --> 01:23:01,542
No, no, no, it's my bet.

1130
01:23:01,611 --> 01:23:06,240
- I just have a good feeling
about that fight.
- A good feeling, huh?

1131
01:23:06,316 --> 01:23:08,943
When did a feeling
return to your head?

1132
01:23:09,019 --> 01:23:11,646
You've outgrown that one.

1133
01:23:11,722 --> 01:23:13,916
Must be all the thinking
