as hot as you can stand.

1354
01:39:43,058 --> 01:39:45,617
Put the razor
in cold water, not hot,

1355
01:39:45,695 --> 01:39:48,424
because metal
does what in cold?

1356
01:39:48,498 --> 01:39:52,866
- I don't know, Johnny.
- That's why I'm telling you!
It contracts.

1357
01:39:55,171 --> 01:39:59,038
That way you get
a first-class shave every time.

1358
01:39:59,109 --> 01:40:01,042
Okay, Johnny.

1359
01:40:03,681 --> 01:40:05,773
Ain't it the life though?

1360
01:40:09,386 --> 01:40:12,946
[ Tom ]
Hello, Sal. You can dangle.

1361
01:40:13,056 --> 01:40:17,659
Hello, Tom. You sure?
You don't look so hot.

1362
01:40:17,660 --> 01:40:19,490
I'm okay.

1363
01:40:22,131 --> 01:40:24,360
I'll drive him home.

1364
01:40:41,418 --> 01:40:43,351
[ Streetcar Rumbling ]

1365
01:40:46,957 --> 01:40:49,186
[ Gunshots ]

1366
01:41:16,920 --> 01:41:19,752
Mr. Reagan, there were shots.

1367
01:41:19,823 --> 01:41:22,757
Go down to the drug store
and call the police.

1368
01:41:24,462 --> 01:41:27,328
You'd better stay there
till the officers arrive.

1369
01:41:28,432 --> 01:41:30,456
Will my cats be all right?

1370
01:41:30,568 --> 01:41:32,592
Yeah, they'll be fine.

1371
01:42:08,473 --> 01:42:10,940
[ Bernie Chuckling ]

1372
01:42:24,388 --> 01:42:27,413
I get it. You set me up.

1373
01:42:27,525 --> 01:42:30,550
Anything to avoid
a little dirty work yourself, huh?

1374
01:42:32,631 --> 01:42:35,963
How'd you know he'd get it
and not me? Or didn't you care?

1375
01:42:36,034 --> 01:42:38,524
I figured you'd come early
looking for blood.

1376
01:42:38,603 --> 01:42:41,537
He wouldn't, so you'd likely
have the drop on him.

1377
01:42:43,174 --> 01:42:47,405
You're right.
The chump never knew what hit him.

1378
01:42:47,479 --> 01:42:50,936
But if you knew
I'd come to kill you,
how do you know I won't still?

1379
01:42:51,016 --> 01:42:54,007
There's nothing in it
for you now.

1380
01:42:54,085 --> 01:42:57,019
With him dead, you and me
got nothing on each other.

1381
01:42:57,990 --> 01:43:00,514
- Let me have the gun.
- Why?

1382
01:43:00,592 --> 01:43:02,957
Pin this on the Dane.

1383
01:43:03,061 --> 01:43:06,029
Neither of us want him
walking around after this.

1384
01:43:06,132 --> 01:43:09,897
The cops'll be Leo's now.
They won't care what
they hang the Dane for.

1385
01:43:09,968 --> 01:43:11,901
I guess that's true,

1386
01:43:11,971 --> 01:43:16,339
if you don't mind keeping
the gun that killed Caspar
and Mink.

1387
01:43:17,442 --> 01:43:19,841
Why did Mink
shoot Rug anyway?

1388
01:43:19,911 --> 01:43:21,901
I don't know.
It was just a mix-up.

1389
01:43:22,013 --> 01:43:24,480
Here.

1390
01:43:27,253 --> 01:43:31,018
- So you're gonna say
the Dane did this?
- Sure.

1391
01:43:31,090 --> 01:43:33,887
Mink thought Rug
was tailing him.

1392
01:43:33,960 --> 01:43:36,519
You know Mink. Hysterical.
Skin full of hop,
head full of boogeymen.

1393
01:43:36,596 --> 01:43:41,157
Comes home crying one day,
saying he had to pop
one of the Dane's spies.

1394
01:43:41,267 --> 01:43:44,827
Rug was tailing Verna,
not Mink. Mink just
happened to be with her.

1395
01:43:44,937 --> 01:43:46,870
[ Laughs ]
Funny, ain't it?

1396
01:43:46,939 --> 01:43:50,169
Mink was terrified
the Dane'd find out me and him
were jungled up together.

1397
01:43:50,242 --> 01:43:53,233
I bet you kept him
worried about that to
keep him under your thumb.

1398
01:43:53,312 --> 01:43:55,745
Yeah, so what?
Scratch, huh?

1399
01:43:55,815 --> 01:43:58,442
A little bonus.

1400
01:43:58,517 --> 01:44:01,952
- Why did Mink take Rug's hair?
- Beats me. The kid was dizzy.

1401
01:44:02,021 --> 01:44:06,150
Fifty-fifty on the dough?
Or maybe I should get more,
since I did the deed.

1402
01:44:08,661 --> 01:44:11,424
Okay, you keep it.
I want you to have it.

1403
01:44:18,237 --> 01:44:23,037
Bernie... we can't pin this
on the Dane.

1404
01:44:23,109 --> 01:44:28,944
- Why not?
- Because the Dane's already
dead halfway across town.

1405
01:44:29,015 --> 01:44:32,245
- What the hell
are you talking about?
- Eddie Dane is dead.

1406
01:44:32,318 --> 01:44:34,251
It's gotta be you.

1407
01:44:35,888 --> 01:44:38,253
I mean, it was your gun.

1408
01:44:38,358 --> 01:44:40,484
[ Chuckling ]

1409
01:44:40,593 --> 01:44:44,790
What is this?
What the hell are you talking about?

1410
01:44:44,865 --> 01:44:47,298
You- -

1411
01:44:47,366 --> 01:44:50,960
You took my gun.
It's just your word against mine.

1412
01:44:52,339 --> 01:44:54,272
[ Clicks ]

1413
01:44:54,341 --> 01:44:56,467
Not necessarily.

1414
01:44:57,577 --> 01:44:59,737
Are you crazy?

1415
01:44:59,846 --> 01:45:03,144
We're square.
You said it yourself.
We got nothing on each other.

1416
01:45:03,216 --> 01:45:05,581
Yep.

1417
01:45:05,652 --> 01:45:10,054
So what's in it for you?
There's no angle.

1418
01:45:10,123 --> 01:45:13,057
You can't just shoot me
like that.

1419
01:45:16,530 --> 01:45:20,021
Jesus Christ,
it don't make sense.

1420
01:45:22,269 --> 01:45:24,202
Tommy--

1421
01:45:26,072 --> 01:45:28,665
Tommy!
[ Sobbing ]

1422
01:45:30,410 --> 01:45:32,343
Look in your heart.

1423
01:45:34,948 --> 01:45:37,711
- Look in your heart.
- What heart?

1424
01:46:14,455 --> 01:46:16,388
[ Dialing Phone ]

1425
01:46:22,730 --> 01:46:24,822
Tad? It's Tom.

1426
01:46:26,200 --> 01:46:29,191
Tell Lazarre
I got his money.

1427
01:46:29,271 --> 01:46:31,295
Yeah, all of it.

1428
01:46:31,405 --> 01:46:34,339
I wanna place a bet
on tonight's fight.

1429
01:46:39,347 --> 01:46:41,280
- They set you up downstairs?
- How's that?

1430
01:46:41,349 --> 01:46:43,475
A little hooch, whatever?

1431
01:46:43,551 --> 01:46:46,485
Thanks for coming, Tom.
Leo's real anxious to see you.

1432
01:46:46,554 --> 01:46:48,646
Yeah, I happened to be near.

1433
01:46:48,723 --> 01:46:50,883
[ Indistinct Shouts ]

1434
01:46:50,992 --> 01:46:54,222
Well, uh, actually this might
not be the best time.

1435
01:46:54,296 --> 01:46:57,230
- Who's he got in there?
- O'Doole and the mayor.

1436
01:46:57,299 --> 01:47:02,065
- I'll try again.
- They're planting the sheeny
tomorrow. You could stop by.

1437
01:47:04,706 --> 01:47:06,639
[ Mumbling Prayer]

1438
01:47:30,933 --> 01:47:34,527
- Big turnout.
- Drop dead.

1439
01:47:34,635 --> 01:47:36,693
She's under a lot of strain.

1440
01:47:36,805 --> 01:47:40,262
- Yeah, well, at least
she didn't hit me.
- [ Chuckles ]

1441
01:47:40,375 --> 01:47:43,741
Glad you came, Tommy.

1442
01:47:43,812 --> 01:47:47,577
- I guess, uh-- Huh?
- She's taking the car.

1443
01:47:52,287 --> 01:47:55,483
- I guess we're walkin'.
- Guess we are.

1444
01:48:00,429 --> 01:48:02,453
We're, uh--
We're getting married.

1445
01:48:05,268 --> 01:48:07,861
Congratulations.

1446
01:48:07,936 --> 01:48:13,168
Funny thing is, she asked me to
tie the knot. I guess you're
not supposed to say that.

1447
01:48:13,275 --> 01:48:16,141
- It doesn't matter.
Congratulations.
- Thanks.

1448
01:48:17,512 --> 01:48:20,446
Hell, Tom, why didn't you
tell me what you were up to?

1449
01:48:20,515 --> 01:48:22,948
I thought you'd
really gone over.

1450
01:48:23,019 --> 01:48:26,613
Not that I didn't deserve it,
but you could've told me.

1451
01:48:26,689 --> 01:48:30,249
Telling you would only
have queered things if it--

1452
01:48:30,326 --> 01:48:33,317
There just wasn't any point.

1453
01:48:33,396 --> 01:48:35,329
I can see that.

1454
01:48:36,733 --> 01:48:39,826
It was a smart play all around.

1455
01:48:39,902 --> 01:48:42,961
I guess you know I'm grateful.

1456
01:48:43,038 --> 01:48:44,971
No need.

1457
01:48:46,708 --> 01:48:49,505
Heh!
I guess you picked
that fight with me...

1458
01:48:49,578 --> 01:48:53,035
just to check yourself
in with Caspar.

1459
01:48:53,115 --> 01:48:56,948
I don't know.
Do you always know
why you do things, Leo?

1460
01:48:57,020 --> 01:48:58,953
Sure I do.

1461
01:49:01,024 --> 01:49:03,719
- It was a smart play.
- Fine.

1462
01:49:06,963 --> 01:49:10,557
Jesus, Tom, I'd do anything
if you'd work for me again.

1463
01:49:10,667 --> 01:49:13,965
I know I've made
some bonehead plays,
I know I can be pigheaded,

1464
01:49:14,037 --> 01:49:16,561
but, damn it, so can you.

1465
01:49:16,640 --> 01:49:21,167
I need you.
Things can be the way they were.

1466
01:49:21,244 --> 01:49:23,541
I know it.
I just know it.

1467
01:49:23,614 --> 01:49:28,209
As for you and Verna,
well, I understand.

1468
01:49:28,318 --> 01:49:31,081
You're both young.

1469
01:49:31,155 --> 01:49:33,452
Damn it, Tom, I forgive you.

1470
01:49:33,524 --> 01:49:35,957
I didn't ask for that,
and I don't want it.

1471
01:49:42,200 --> 01:49:44,133
Good-bye, Leo.


